    "summary": "LAND+ was founded in support of a new vision on sustainable agriculture and food production, replacing high-input monoculture farming with an ecosystem approach, allowing for the creative forces of nature to give rise to \u2018living landscapes\u2019 with robust and diverse plant and animal communities and stable carbon stocks to sustain livelihoods around the world.  \n\nWith such ecosystems approach still considered \u2018alternative\u2019 to high-input monoculture farming, LAND+ is motivated by the urgency of its adoption into mainstream farming practice as a future-proof and effective answer to climate change and food, health and environmental crises around the world.      \n\nThe following link provides access to a detailed account by Mark Shepard, who, as a true pioneer, has gone far beyond fashionable \u2018feel good\u2019 activities with his concept of \u2018Restoration Agriculture\u2019 developed on his New Forest Farm in Wisconsin, United States.\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kb_t-sVVzF0",
